[2] Ethiopia, 1 newly confirmed case - OCHA, Relief Web
Date: Fri 17 Mar 2014
Source: UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA), Relief Web [summ., edited]
http://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/Humanitarian%20Bulletin_17%20March%202014.pdf


A new case of wild poliovirus was confirmed in Warder woreda [district], Dollo zone (Somali region) with a [5 Jan 2014] date of onset. A joint investigation team is conducting an investigation into the 10th case [there were 9 confirmed cases of WPV1 in Ethiopia in 2013, so this case is the 10th associated with the ongoing outbreak in the Horn of Africa. - Mod.MPP], a 25-month-old male who reportedly received 7 oral polio vaccine doses. An additional round of the supplementary immunization activity (SIA), targeting more than 4 million children under 15 in Somali region and other high-risk areas, was planned for [14-17 Mar 2014].

--
Communicated by:
Ota Masaki, MD, PhD
<otam@jata.or.jp>

